content_vision: At the end, only one is left standing. In the end, she realizes that she is stronger alone.
text:
Intro:
I'm not here to compete or impress,
just living my truth, no need to confess.

Verse 1:
Looking back at the past, I see how far I've come,
and I know I'm better off without those who once left me numb.
Every scar and every tear, only reminds
me of the strength that's always been here.
Through the pain and the struggle, I found my voice,
and now I'm standing tall, it's my choice.
I'm unstoppable, I've got nothing to hide,
my strength shines through, I won't be denied.

Pre-Chorus 1:
I won't let anyone hold me back, I am my own strength and I won't crack,
my truth is my power, it's what I lack.

Chorus 1:
I don't need anyone's validation, my strength is my salvation,
I'll stand tall and proud, my inner fire blazing,
I am the one who's left standing, triumphant and free,
my own hero, that's all I'll ever need.

Verse 2:
I used to think I needed someone else, to make me whole and take away my pain,
but now I know, I've always been complete, and that's the truth that keeps me sane.
I used to think I needed someone else, to make me whole and take away my pain,
but now I see, I've had the power within, my inner strength, my truth, my gain.
They said I couldn't do it on my own, that I needed someone by my side,
but now I see, I've always been enough, my own strength, my own guide.
They said I couldn't do it on my own, that I needed someone by my side,
but now I've proved them wrong, my strength shines brighter than any pride.

Chorus 2:
I won't back down, I'll fight for my place,
cause in the end, I am my greatest saving grace.
I'll rise from the ashes, unbreakable and strong,
I am my own anchor, my own guiding song.

Bridge:
I used to think I needed you, but now I see, I'm better off alone,
with my strength and my truth, I can stand on my own.
But now I see the truth, I was holding myself back,
thinking I needed someone, but it was my own strength that I lacked.

Outro:
In the end, I found my own strength and it's all I'll ever need,
my own hero, triumphant indeed.

Theme melody:
But in the end, I found the true melody within myself,
my own symphony, my own masterpiece.

Solo:
So I stand alone, unbreakable and strong,
my truth is my armor, my will, my song.

Intro:
Caught up in this twisted game, looking for someone to blame,
but now I see, I am my own flame.

Verse 1:
Sweatin' blood, tears and fears, but I won't back down,
can't break this fire inside, I'll wear my crown.
I dance in the flames, fueled by my pain,
but at the end of the day, I'll rise again.
But when the ashes settle, I'll stand tall and proud,
stronger than ever, I'll scream it loud.
No longer seeking someone else's validation,
I've found my own worth, my own salvation.

Pre-Chorus 1:
Lost in the haze, I couldn't see,
blinded by your love and your sweet deceit.

Chorus 1:
Like a phoenix rising from the ashes of my past,
I'll spread my wings, and soar at last.
I've burned down bridges, left behind my past,
but now I'm rising strong, this love will last.

Verse 2:
I've been down this road before, feeling lost in the abyss,
but now I've found my way, and I won't be dismissed.
But now I see, I am my own rock and roll star,
standing strong on my own two feet.
But I found my voice, in the midst of the noise,
and now I'll sing my truth, no longer coy.
But through the chaos and the noise, I found my true voice,
and now I'll rise above, it's my time to rejoice.

Chorus 2:
But at the end of it all, I realized that being alone was my greatest strength,
I'll stand tall and proud, embracing my independence.
But I refuse to let anyone dim my light,
I'll keep shining on, unstoppable and bright.

Bridge:
I may have stumbled, and fallen to the ground,
but now I stand tall, with my head held high, unbound.
Through all the battles and the pain,
I found my strength and learned to reign.

Outro:
But in the end, I am my own savior,
my own knight,

Theme melody:
As I stand alone, the last one left in this game,
I realize my worth and my incredible strength.

Solo:
I take back my power and rise up from the dirt,
stronger alone, but now with a heart that won't hurt.

Intro:
It starts with a spark, burning deep inside,
but by the end, I'll be the last one to survive.

Verse 1:
A voice that whispered, 'you can't do this on your own,'
but I found my strength when all others had flown.
I followed my heart, despite the doubts and fears,
and now I stand tall, the last one still here.
Battles may come, hardships may arise,
but I'll stand my ground, despite the lies.
For in my journey of self-discovery and growth,
I found my strength, surpassing all oaths.

Pre-Chorus 1:
I never needed anyone to hold my hand,
I'll stand on my own, proud and grand.

Chorus 1:
So I'll stand tall, with my head held high,
leaving all my doubts and fears behind.
I'll keep rising, defying all odds,
leaving behind all the naysayers and frauds.

Verse 2:
Through the hardships and tears, I stood my ground, never giving in,
For I am strong, and my resilience is my greatest win.
I spread my wings and flew, soaring to new heights,
no longer bound by anyone's expectations or slights.
Through the struggles and battles, I fought with all my might,
facing my fears head on, unafraid to ignite.
But as I stand here now, with my head held high,
I know I'm better off without any ties.

Chorus 2:
Never thought I'd find the strength to stand alone,

But as I stand here now, with my head held high,
I know I'm better off without any ties.
I'll keep rising, with fire in my soul,
proving to myself that I am whole.

Bridge:
I used to think I needed someone else by my side,
But now I see, alone is where I'll thrive.
But now I see, being alone doesn't mean being lonely,
I own my strength, and I'm the one and only.

Outro:
Alone but not lonely, I'll keep rising above all the noise,
for I've found my strength in being my own choice.

I used to think love was my weakness,
but now I see it's my greatest strength,

Solo:

I embrace my strength, no longer needing to win.

but in the end, I stand tall, a testament to my own devotion.

a symbol of my will

Outro:
